\section{Power rules}
Keeping the answer in power form, simplify the following expression:
\begin{table}[h!]
\centering
\begin{tabular}{c c c}
\hspace{5cm} & \hspace{5cm} & \hspace{5cm} \\
a) ${5}^{8}\times{5}^{3}$ & b) ${9}^{-4}\times{9}^{-2}$ & c) ${7}^{-7}\times{7}^{-1}$ \\ \\
d) ${2}^{4}\div{2}^{5}$ & e) ${6}^{-4}\div{6}^{-4}$ & f) ${5}^{-8}\div{5}^{-3}$ \\ \\
g) $({6}^{10})^{4}$ & h) $({6}^{2})^{-7}$ & i) $({-419})^1$ \\ \\
\end{tabular}
\end{table}
\newline
Simplify the following expression into fractions. Fully simplify your answer where possible:
\begin{table}[h!]
\centering
\begin{tabular}{c c c}
\hspace{5cm} & \hspace{5cm} & \hspace{5cm} \\
a) ${5}^{-2}$ & b) ${2}^{-1}\times{2}^{-3}$ & c) ${2}^{-3} - {2}^{-3}$ \\ \\
\end{tabular}
\end{table}
\newline
Rewrite the following expressions into surds:
\begin{table}[h!]
\centering
\begin{tabular}{c c c}
\hspace{5cm} & \hspace{5cm} & \hspace{5cm} \\
a) ${64}^\frac{1}{{3}}$ & b) ${9}^\frac{1}{{3}}$ & c) ${81}^\frac{1}{{2}}$ \\ \\
\end{tabular}
\end{table}
